s, Urban Planning & Policy (UPP) at UIC has led the way in preparing students for careers for over 40 years. Grounded in social equity and sustainability, we teach students to use innovative concepts and technology to address urban issues.  UIC planning students take all classes in Chicago, study in Chicago, and live and breathe in Chicago.  Where better to learn the art of planning great cities than in the city of Daniel Burnham?      CUPPA 40th Anniversary Video           Graduate Deadlines Extended  Master in Urban Planning and Policy and Master in City Design deadline extended             What's UPP: 2019 In Review             UPP 40th Anniversary Video             CUPPA: Transforming Urban Life           Planetizen Urban Planning Program Rankings      The Planetizen Guide to Graduate Urban Planning Programs recognizes the Department of Urban Planning and Policy as being ranked among the top 20 urban planning programs in the United States.  #17 Overall Graduate Urban Planning Program  #16 According to Urban Planning Educators  #11 Top Public Programs  #8 Top Big City Programs  #3 in the Midwest  #7 Among programs that offer part-time study  #3 Most Alumni            Undergraduate Programs           BA in Urban Studies             Joint Urban Studies & Master of Urban Planning             Minor in Urban Studies             Minor in Sustainable Cities             Minor in Geographic Information Systems          Graduate Programs           Master in Urban Planning and Policy             Master of City Design             MUPP/MPH Dual Degree Program             Doctorate in Urban Planning & Policy             Geospatial Analysis and Visualization Certificate             Public Transit Planning and Management Certificate           Apply Now       UIC Master of Urban Planning and Policy      UIC’s Master of Urban Planning and Policy program is the only accredited planning program in the Chicagoland region by the Planning Accreditation Board (PAB) . According to the PAB, accreditation is a system for recognizing educational institutions for performance, integrity and quality. Accreditation ensures high quality education for future urban planners.  We are also proud members of the Association of Collegiate Schools of Planning (ACSP) , Association of European Schools of Planning (AESOP) and the American Planning Association (APA) .       UPP News and Events            UPP's Janet Smith Receives Marilyn J. Gittell Activist Scholar Award    Posted on May 08, 2020             Joshua Drucker And Rachel Weber Co-author Essay for PA Times On TIF Use And The Great Recession    Posted on May 05, 2020             Dean Pagano Discusses Pandemic's Economic Impact On Cincinnati Edition    Posted on May 05, 2020             UPP’s Professor Betancur Provides Perspective in Pilsen Documentary    Posted on April 30, 2020             UDVL Partners With Institute Of Government And Public Affairs To Create Tool To Measure Human Toll Of Pandemic    Posted on April 28, 2020           May  16  2020      Virtual CUPPA Commencement Celebration!     Saturday, 12:00 am–11:59 pm   Virtual.  Website location coming soon.            More News and Events        Document icon           More news        Calendar icon        More events          Follow Us     Follow Us       Follow Us              Department of Urban Planning and Policy    Back to main content           UPP Admissions & Programs     BA in Urban Studies    Joint BA in Urban Studies & Master of Urban Planning and Policy    Minor in Urban Studies    Minor in Geographic Information Systems    Minor in Sustainable Cities    Master of City Design    Master in Urban Planning and Policy    MUPP/MPH Dual Degree Program    Public Information    Doctorate in Urban Planning & Policy    Urban Planning and Policy Certificate Programs     Geospatial Analysis and Visualization (GSAV) Certificate    Public Transit Planning and Management (PTPM) Certificate        UPP News    UPP Events    UPP People    UPP Student